Implement ticket status commands: start, done, cancel, archive.

`chipper start <id>`:
- Fail if ticket id does not exist.
- Fail if another ticket is already in_progress and specify which one is in progress.
- Mark ticket in_progress in chipper-queue
- Run git integration (see git-integration ticket)

`chipper done`:
- if no ticket is in progress, emit failure message and exit
- Mark current ticket done in chipper-queue
- WRONG: Append AI-generated summary to the ticket file (decisions made, actions taken, context)
  - this doesn't make sense. Chipper is not running AI.
  - if the AI is running the chipper commands, it can append stuff to the file if it wants.
  - but chipper is only dealing with files and git commits, no AI stuff.
- Run git integration (see git-integration ticket)

`chipper cancel <id>`:
- Mark ticket cancelled in chipper-queue

`chipper archive <id>`:
- Mark ticket archived in chipper-queue
- Archived tickets are excluded from active queue views

commands accept the full ticket ID (e.g. CHP-login) or just the slug (login).
But the done command expects that in this directory zero or one tickets are active at a time.
And if zero fails.

Depends on: cli-scaffolding, manifest-implementation
